<paragraph id="D60E45CE90011A8131EF416B3D005BB3" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="69B8584C6EE21BBD16B34C1B6B934341" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
In its morphological characters, 
<taxonomicName id="26D8A8368F2DF591DFF7B075803CA200" genus="G." lsidName="G. penicillioides" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="penicillioides">
<emphasis id="68D5AC6EA05384EB0136DECCA1B9A514" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. penicillioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName id="13C9F48C68B2F682E94C25BA7120AD42" genus="G." lsidName="G. scorpioides" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" rank="species" species="scorpioides">
<emphasis id="B1310740796E2B6C97FA1B1B717E29EB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">G. scorpioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
